gw.api.builder

Class PolicyLocationBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.databuilder.DataBuilder<PolicyLocation,PolicyLocationBuilder>
      • gw.api.builder.PolicyLocationBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ValueGenerator<PolicyLocation>

    public class PolicyLocationBuilder
extends DataBuilder<PolicyLocation,PolicyLocationBuilder>
    Builder for a PolicyLocation. PolicyLocation is an EffDated, so this has to be built in the context of a PolicyPeriod (probably a subclass of JobBuilder). Typical usages would be 
       new JobBuilderSubclass().withPrimaryPolicyLocation(new PolicyLocationBuilder())
   new JobBuilderSubclass().withPolicyLocation(new PolicyLocationBuilder())
    where the JobBuilderSubclass might be SubmissionBuilder, PolicyChangeBuilder, RenewalBuilder, etc. 
       new PolicyLocationBuilder().onPeriod(period)
    is also allowed. Attempting to build a PolicyLocation with another context, however, will result in an IllegalStateException. Building without a context (i.e. new PolicyLocation().create()) will also throw IllegalStateException.

    PolicyLocationBuilder defines an explicit populator which runs at the maximum priority (i.e. last); its purpose is to supply an AccountLocation if none was specified. There are also a number of fields that are set with their own populators, which run at DEFAULT_ORDER.

    The new PolicyLocation created by this builder will be auto-numbered, and will have an auto-number sequence for its Buildings as well.
